China Metal Chairman Ho Resigns After Taiwan Court Judgment

-- B y   B e n   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-10-09T10:25:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-09/china-metal-chairman-ho-resigns-after-taiwan-court-judgment.html
China Metal International Holdings
said Chairman Ho Ming-Shiann has resigned following his
conviction by a Taiwan court in a breach of trust case unrelated
to the company.  China Metal said that the judgment would have no “adverse
financial and operational impact.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Richardson at 
 brichardson8@bloomberg.net  